 Tottenham Hotspur youngster Luke Amos is reportedly on the radar of Queens Park Rangers. According to Football.London, Queens Park Rangers will sign Luke Amos from Tottenham Hotspur in the summer transfer window. It has been reported that Championship outfit QPR will recruit Amos on a season-long loan deal from Premier League club Tottenham. Amos is a very good and promising young midfielder whose hunger and dynamism will help Mark Warburton’s side. The 22-year-old midfielder has played in the lower leagues with Southend United and Stevenage, and he can be an important player for QPR working under Warburton. The post QPR Will Sign Tottenham Hotspur’s Luke Amos On Loan  Source: Independent